transcript.text: Hello, welcome back to the On Print Shop Designer Studio tutorial series.
Today we will be walking you through the steps to create a PDF block path for curved text using the Illustrator tool.
In Illustrator, creating curved text along a block path involves using the text tool and shaping the text manually.
This method provides you with greater control over the text appearance and positioning.
Here's how you can achieve this.
Open your file in Illustrator.
You can use the pen tool to draw a path.
Now you can add anchor points using pen tool and create a path with your preferred shape and then edit the path by dragging its nodes and make your design accordingly.
You can set the properties of the path using the stroke.
Once done, you need to copy the path and paste it into a new document.
You can use the shortcut Control plus N to open a new document and Control plus we to paste the path into the new document.
Next, select the artboard tool to resize the page according to the path size.
Now navigate to the preset menu and select Fit to selected art.
Select the path and save it as an SVG format.
Select SVG from the drop down menu.
Once done, click on the Save button.
Finally, check the settings for SVG format.
Now go back to Original design and save the file in PDF format by selecting PDF from the drop down menu and then clicking on the Save button.
Your document will be saved on the given path.
For further steps, open the SVG document using Edit with Notepad.
Copy this path to paste it into the Custom Properties window in the PDF Block plugin.
Now open your PDF file with Adobe Acrobat and navigate to the PDF Lib Blocks menu.
Draw one text block using the PDF Lib Block plugin.

While drawing this block, consider the below points #1 block should cover the highest left of the path #2 block should cover the highest right of the path #3 block should cover the highest bottom of the path #4 block should cover the highest top of the path.
At the end, match the right, left, and bottom blocks perfectly with the borders of the path.
Once set, click on the Expand All button.
Now it is time to set the block properties.
Using the Property window, enter your preferred text in the default text area.
Set alignment of the text.
Now the PDF file is ready for upload.
Save the file from the File menu.
Add a clip path to the Image block using Manage Properties and you have successfully created the block PDF path in the Illustrator tool.
Hope you enjoyed the video.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
